{"word":"θρασύνω","slug":"θρασύνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θρασύνω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θρασύς'><el>θρασύς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>= <a href='S:θαρσύνω'><el>θαρσύνω</el></a>, <i>to make bold, embolden, encourage</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> and <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <i>to be bold</i> or <i>ready, take courage</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, in bad sense, <i>to be over-bold, audacious, to speak boldly</i> or <i>insolently</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}